.TH "BROWSE" "1" "" "" ""
.hy
.SH NAME
.PP
browse - A multi-file pager with recursive navigation.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
browse [-fFinv] [-p pattern] [-t title] [filename\&...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Browse and search text files, follow changes.
.PP
\f[B]browse\f[R] is an interactive pager for navigating \f[I]sets of
files\f[R], not just viewing one file at a time.
.PP
Unlike traditional pagers, \f[B]browse\f[R] lets you temporarily switch
to a new set of files and then return exactly where you left off.
This recursive browsing model makes it natural to explore logs, search
results, source trees, and related files without losing context.
.PP
\f[B]Think:\f[R] \f[V]less\f[R] + \f[V]pushd/popd\f[R] for files.
.SS Why Use Browse?
.IP \[bu] 2
Explore multiple files as one workflow.
.IP \[bu] 2
Drill into a new file set and return to your previous place.
.IP \[bu] 2
Browse command output from pipelines as if it were a file.
.IP \[bu] 2
Use keyboard-driven navigation, search, shell commands, and history.
.IP \[bu] 2
Keep your context while investigating logs, source, or generated
results.
.SS Features
.SS Navigation Features
.IP \[bu] 2
Forward and reverse paging.
.IP \[bu] 2
Continuous scrolling in both directions.
.IP \[bu] 2
Horizontal scrolling for wide lines.
.IP \[bu] 2
Jump to line numbers.
.IP \[bu] 2
Mark pages and jump back to them.
.IP \[bu] 2
Follow and tail modes for changing files.
.SS Search and Exploration
.IP \[bu] 2
Forward and reverse regex search.
.IP \[bu] 2
Case-sensitive and case-insensitive search.
.IP \[bu] 2
Pattern highlighting.
.IP \[bu] 2
Search pattern history.
.IP \[bu] 2
Run \f[V]grep\f[R] on the current file in a nested browse session.
.SS Multi-File Workflow
.IP \[bu] 2
Browse multiple files from the command line.
.IP \[bu] 2
Browse standard input as a temporary file.
.IP \[bu] 2
Open nested file sets with \f[V]B\f[R].
.IP \[bu] 2
Return from nested file sets with \f[V]x\f[R] or \f[V]X\f[R].
.IP \[bu] 2
Rewind the active file list with \f[V]Ctrl+R\f[R].
.IP \[bu] 2
Show the current remaining file list with \f[V]a\f[R].
.SS Convenience
.IP \[bu] 2
File and directory completion.
.IP \[bu] 2
Shell escape with command completion.
.IP \[bu] 2
Persistent file, directory, search, and shell histories.
.IP \[bu] 2
Session saving and restoration.
.IP \[bu] 2
Run \f[V]fmt -s\f[R] on the current file in a nested browse session.
.IP \[bu] 2
Built-in help screen.
.SS Usage
.PP
Browse one or more files:
.nf

browse file1.log file2.log file3.log
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
Browse shell-expanded globs:
.nf

browse *.go
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
Browse results from a pipeline:
.nf

grep -rl timeout /var/log | browse
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
Start with an initial search pattern:
.nf

browse -p ERROR app.log
\f[R]
.fi
