.TE
.SS Configuration and History
.PP
\f[B]browse\f[R] stores configuration and history in:
.nf

\[ti]/.browse/
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
The session file is:
.nf

\[ti]/.browse/browserc
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
It saves:
.IP \[bu] 2
Current file name.
.IP \[bu] 2
First line on the page.
.IP \[bu] 2
Search pattern.
.IP \[bu] 2
Marks.
.IP \[bu] 2
Page title.
.PP
History files:
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[V]\[ti]/.browse/browse_dirs\f[R] - directory history.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[V]\[ti]/.browse/browse_files\f[R] - file browsing history.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[V]\[ti]/.browse/browse_search\f[R] - search pattern history.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[V]\[ti]/.browse/browse_shell\f[R] - shell command history.
.SS Limitations
.IP \[bu] 2
Xterm-specific behavior.
.IP \[bu] 2
Logical lines are truncated to screen width.
.IP \[bu] 2
Long lines are internally capped at about 4K.
.IP \[bu] 2
Tabs are converted to spaces.
.IP \[bu] 2
Non-printable characters may display poorly.
.IP \[bu] 2
Terminal title handling may vary by environment.
